      • run

        public ExitStatus run()
        This first prints out the current breakpoint source location before calling the superclass' run method. The synchronization prevents more than one debugging session on the console.
        Returns:
        the exit status

      • doEvaluate

        protected boolean doEvaluate(String line)
        Evaluate an expression in the breakpoint's context. This is similar to the superclass method, except that the context is the one taken from the breakpoint, and the execution is not timed.
